# There are several MPI libraries available. Here, we set the desired
# "mpif90" script to use during compilation. This only works if the make
# configuration file (say, Linux-pgi.mk) in the "Compilers" directory
# has the following definition for FC (Fortran Compiler) in the USE_MPI
# section:
#
#              FC := mpif90
#
# that is, "mpif90" defined without any path. Notice that the path
# where the MPI library is installed is computer dependent. Recall
# that you still need to use the appropriate "mpirun" to execute.[m

[34m############################################################################
# Additional libraries selections.
#
# If the USE_MY_LIBS is activated above, the path of the libraries
# required by ROMS can be set here using environmental variables
# which take precedence to the values specified in the make macro
# definitions file (Compilers/*.mk). For most applications, only
# the location of the NetCDF library is needed during compilation.
#
# Notice that when the USE_NETCDF4 macro is activated, we need the
# serial or parallel version of the NetCDF-4/HDF5 library. The
# configuration script NF_CONFIG (available since NetCDF 4.0.1)
# is used to set up all the required libraries according to the
# installed options (openDAP, netCDF4/HDF5 file format). The
# parallel library uses the MPI-I/O layer (usually available
# in MPICH2 and OpenMPI) requiring compiling with the selected
# MPI library.
#
# In ROMS distributed-memory applications, you may use either the
# serial or parallel version of the NetCDF-4/HDF5 library. The
# parallel version is required when parallel I/O is activated
# (ROMS cpp option PARALLEL_IO and HDF5).
#
# However, in serial or shared-memory ROMS applications, we need
# to use the serial version of the NetCDF-4/HDF5 to avoid conflicts
# with the compiler. We cannot activate MPI constructs in serial
# or shared-memory ROMS code. Hybrid parallelism is not possible.
#
# Recall also that the MPI library comes in several flavors:
# MPICH, MPICH2, OpenMPI, etc.[m[49;166H253,7[9C51%[6;7H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[6;7H[49;156H   [6;5H[27m[23m[29m[m[H[2J[1;1H[34m# Recall also that the MPI library comes in several flavors:
# MPICH, MPICH2, OpenMPI, etc.[m

[38;5;130mif [[m [38;5;130m-n[m [38;5;130m"[m[35m${USE_MY_LIBS[m[38;5;130m:+1[m[35m}[m[38;5;130m"[m [38;5;130m];[m [38;5;130mthen
[m  [38;5;130mcase[m [38;5;130m"[m[35m$FORT[m[38;5;130m"[m [38;5;130min[m
    ifort [38;5;130m)[7;7Hexport[m[36m             ESMF_OS=[mLinux[8;7H[38;5;130mexport[m[36m       ESMF_COMPILER=[mifort[9;7H[38;5;130mexport[m[36m [38;5;130m"[m[35m${USE_MPI[m[38;5;130m:+1[m[35m}[m[38;5;130m"[m [38;5;130m];[m [38;5;130mthen[16;9Hif [[m [38;5;130m"[m[35m${which_MPI}[m[38;5;130m"[m [38;5;130m=[m [34m############################################################################
# Header and other source directories selections.
#
# The rest of this script sets the path to the users header file and
# analytical source files, if any. See the templates in User/Functionals.
#
# If applicable, use the MY_ANALYTICAL_DIR directory to place your
# customized biology model header file (like fennel.h, nemuro.h, ecosim.h,
# etc).[m

  [38;5;130mexport[m[36m     MY_HEADER_DIR=[m[35m${MY_PROJECT_DIR}[m/Projects/Trench
  [38;5;130mexport[m[36m MY_ANALYTICAL_DIR=[m[35m${MY_PROJECT_DIR}[m/Projects/Trench
[34m#   export     MY_HEADER_DIR=${MY_PROJECT_DIR}/Projects/Inlet_test/Coupled
#   export MY_ANALYTICAL_DIR=${MY_PROJECT_DIR}/Projects/Inlet_test/Coupled

# Put the binary to execute in the following directory.

# export            BINDIR=${MY_PROJECT_DIR}[m
  [38;5;130mexport[m[36m            BINDIR=[m./

[34m# Put the f90 files in a project specific Build directory to avoid conflict
# with other projects.

# export       SCRATCH_DIR=${MY_PROJECT_DIR}/Build[m
  [38;5;130mexport[m[36m       SCRATCH_DIR=[m./Build

[34m# Go to the users source directory to compile. The options set above will
# pick up the application-specific code from the appropriate place.

############################################################################
# End of USER definitions area.  You really should not change anything 
# down here.
#[m
 [38;5;130mcd[m [35m${MY_ROMS_SRC}[m

[34m#--------------------------------------------------------------------------[m[49;166H437,9[9C90%[6;9H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[6;9H[49;156H   [6;1H[27m[23m[29m[m[H[2J[2;1H[34m#--------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Compile.
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Remove build directory.[m

[38;5;130mif [[m [35m$clean[m [38;5;130m-eq[m [31m1[m [38;5;130m];[m [38;5;130mthen[m
  make clean
[38;5;130mfi[m

[34m# Compile (the binary will go to BINDIR set above).

# first go to make some coupler files[m
  make mct_params
  [38;5;130mcd[m [35m${SCRATCH_DIR}[m
  [38;5;130mexport[m[36m MCT_PARAMS_DIR=[m[35m${PWD}[m
  [38;5;130mcd[m [35m${MY_ROMS_SRC}[m

  [38;5;130mexport[m[36m WRF_DIR=[m[35m${MY_ROMS_SRC}[m/WRF
[38;5;130mif [[m [35m$cleanwrf[m [38;5;130m-eq[m [31m1[m [38;5;130m];[m [38;5;130mthen[m
  make wrfclean
  [38;5;130mcd[m [35m${MY_ROMS_SRC}[m
[38;5;130mfi[m
  make wrf

  [38;5;130mexport[m[36m WRFHYDRO_DIR=[m[35m${MY_ROMS_SRC}[m/WRF/hydro_v3.[31m0[m
[38;5;130mif [[m [35m$cleanwrfhydro[m [38;5;130m-eq[m [31m1[m [38;5;130m];[m [38;5;130mthen[m
  make wrfhydroclean
  [38;5;130mcd[m [35m${MY_ROMS_SRC}[m
[38;5;130mfi[m
  make wrfhydro

[38;5;130mif [[m [35m$cleanww3[m [38;5;130m-eq[m [31m1[m [38;5;130m];[m [38;5;130mthen[m
  make ww3clean
  [38;5;130mcd[m [35m${MY_ROMS_SRC}[m
[38;5;130mfi[m
  make ww3

[38;5;130mif [[m [35m$dprint[m [38;5;130m-eq[m [31m1[m [38;5;130m];[m [38;5;130mthen[m
  make [35m$debug[m
[38;5;130melse
[m  [38;5;130mif [[m [35m$parallel[m [38;5;130m-eq[m [31m1[m [38;5;130m];[m [38;5;130mthen[m
    make [35m$NCPUS[m
  [38;5;130melse[m
    make
  [38;5;130mfi
fi[m

[?2004h[?1049h[22;0;0t[?1h=[?2004h[1;49r[?12h[?12l[27m[23m[29m[m[H[2J[?25l[49;1H"ww3_swan_input.m" [dos] 138L, 5089C[2;1H▽[6n[2;1H  [1;1H[>c]10;?]11;?[1;1H[34m% script ww3_swan_input.m
%
% This script is the main driver to 
% download, convert and interpolate WW3 data to TPAR input for SWAN.
%
% Written 4/23/09 by Brandy Armstrong
% some mods, jcwarner Arpil 27, 2009
%
% READ THE INSTRUCTIONS IN THE COAWST MANUAL 
% FOR SWAN BC's SECTION 10.
%
% First, acquire the necessary grib files from
% ftp://polar.ncep.noaa.gov/pub/history/waves/
%

% ************* BEGIN USER INPUT   ****************************

%1) Enter WORKING DIRECTORY.
% This is the location of ww3 grb files downloaded and the
% location of output for the TPAR files to be created.
% ***WARNING***
% The TPAR files created are saved in the working directory and are named
% generically (numbered). Any existing TPAR files will be overwritten !!!!
%[m
working_dir=[31m'D:\COAWST_tests\sandy_for_workshop\Projects\Sandy'[m
[36meval[m([36m[[m[31m'cd '[m,working_dir,[31m';'[m[36m][m)[35m;[m

[34m%2) Enter dates of data requested.[m
yearww3=[31m'2012'[m[35m;[m    [34m%input year of data yyyy [m
mmww3=[31m'10'[m[35m;[m[7C[34m%input month of data mm[m
ddww3=[31m'00'[m[35m;[m[8C[34m%keep this as '00'

%3) Enter the ww3 grid area[m
ww3_area=[31m'multi_1.at_10m'[m[35m;[m    [34m%western north atlantic

%4) Enter path\name of SWAN netcdf grid. This is typically the same
% as the roms grid.[m
modelgrid=[31m'D:/COAWST_tests/sandy_for_workshop/Projects/Sandy/Sandy_roms_grid.nc'[m[35m;[m

[34m%5) Enter the spacings of TPAR file locations around the perimeter
% of the grid. One TPAR file every 'specres' point.
% ww3_specpoints assumes masking of 0 for land and NaN for water[m
specres=[31m10[m[35m;[m [34m% spec point resolution

% flag for simulations that change month (e.g., goes from October 10 to
% November 20)[m
long_run=[31m0[m[35m;[m  [34m% DEFAULT

[1;49r[48;13H[38;5;130mwhile[m [31m1[m[49;166H[K[49;166H117,1[9C82%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;17Htline = fgetl(pfid)[35m;[m[49;166H[K[49;166H118,1[9C83%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;17H[38;5;130mif[m [38;5;130m~[mischar(tline), [38;5;130mbreak[m, [38;5;130mend[m[49;166H[K[49;166H119,1[9C84%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;17Hdata=[36m[[mdata[35m;[mstr2num(tline)[36m][m[35m;[m[49;166H[K[49;166H120,1[9C85%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;13H[38;5;130mend[m[49;166H[K[49;166H121,1[9C86%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;13Hfclose(pfid)[35m;[m[49;166H[K[49;166H122,1[9C87%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;9H[38;5;130mend[m[49;166H[K[49;166H123,1[9C88%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;9H[36m[[mCA,IA,IC[36m][m = unique(data(:,[31m1[m))[35m;[m[49;166H[K[49;166H124,1[9C90%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;9Hdata=data(IA,:)[35m;[m[49;166H[K[49;166H125,1[9C91%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[49;166H[K[49;166H126,1[9C92%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;9H[36m[[mpfid,message[36m][m=fopen(D(itp).name,[31m'w'[m)[35m;[m[49;166H[K[49;166H127,1[9C93%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;9Hfprintf(fid,[31m'TPAR \n'[m)[35m;[m[49;166H[K[49;166H128,1[9C94%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;9Hfprintf(pfid,[31m'%8.4f %3.2f %3.2f %3.f. %2.f\n'[m,data[38;5;130m'[m)[35m;[m[49;166H[K[49;166H129,1[9C95%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;9Hfclose(pfid)[35m;[m[49;166H[K[49;166H130,1[9C96%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;5H[38;5;130mend[m[49;166H[K[49;166H131,1[9C97%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;1H[38;5;130mend[m[49;166H[K[49;166H132,1[9C98%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[49;166H[K[49;166H133,1[9CBot[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [44;1H[49;168H4[44;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[44;1H[49;156H   [45;1H[49;168H5[45;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[45;1H[49;156H   [46;1H[49;168H6[46;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[46;1H[49;156H   [47;1H[49;168H7[47;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[47;1H[49;156H   [48;1H[49;168H8,0-1[48;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[48;1H[49;156H   [48;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[48;1H[49;156H   [48;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[48;1H[49;156H   [48;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[48;1H[49;156H   [48;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[48;1H[49;156H   [48;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[48;1H[49;156H   [48;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[48;1H[49;156H   [43;9H[27m[23m[29m[m[H[2J[1;1H[34m% flag for simulations that change month (e.g., goes from October 10 to
% November 20)[m
long_run=[31m0[m[35m;[m  [34m% DEFAULT
%long_run=1;[m
[38;5;130mif[m long_run
    total_number_months=[31m2[m[35m;[m [34m% total number of months [7;25H% (not the length of the run, but rather the number[8;25H% of grib files)[m
[38;5;130mend[m

[34m% *************END OF USER INPUT****************************[m

[38;5;130mif[m [38;5;130m~[mlong_run
    [34m% Call routine to compute TPAR files.[m
    ww3gb_2TPAR(modelgrid,yearww3,mmww3,ww3_area,ddww3,specres)[17;5H[34m% After creating the TPAR files, tell the user what info is needed to 
[m    [34m% be added to INPUT file.
[m    [34m% Write out boundary file lines for INPUT file[m
    bdry_com [34m%script writes out file Bound_spec_command to working directory[m
    display([31m'BOUNDSPEC command lines can be found in the file Bound_spec_command'[m)[35m;[m
    display([31m'You must copy the lines from that file into your SWAN INPUT file'[m)[35m;[m
[38;5;130melse[m
    [36meval[m([36m[[m[31m'!mkdir '[m,yearww3,mmww3[36m][m)[26;5H[34m% Call routine to compute TPAR files.[m
    ww3gb_2TPAR(modelgrid,yearww3,mmww3,ww3_area,ddww3,specres)[29;5H[34m% After creating the TPAR files, tell the user what info is needed to 
[m    [34m% be added to INPUT file.
[m    [34m% Write out boundary file lines for INPUT file[m
    bdry_com [34m%script writes out file Bound_spec_command to working directory[m
    display([31m'BOUNDSPEC command lines can be found in the file Bound_spec_command'[m)[35m;[m
    display([31m'You must copy the lines from that file into your SWAN INPUT file'[m)[35m;[m[36;5H[36meval[m([36m[[m[31m'!mv TPAR*.txt '[m,yearww3,mmww3,[31m'/.'[m[36m][m)[38;5H[38;5;130mfor[m im=[31m1[m:total_number_months[38;5;130m-[m[31m1[m[39;9Hyymm=datestr(datenum(str2double(yearww3),str2double(mmww3)[38;5;130m+[mim,[31m1[m),[31m'yyyymm'[m)[35m;[m[40;9H[36meval[m([36m[[m[31m'!mkdir '[m,yymm[36m][m)[42;9H[34m% Call routine to compute TPAR files.[m[43;9Hww3gb_2TPAR(modelgrid,yymm([31m1[m:[31m4[m),yymm([31m5[m:[31m6[m),ww3_area,ddww3,specres)[45;9Hbdry_com [34m%script writes out file Bound_spec_command to working directory[m[46;9Hdisplay([31m'BOUNDSPEC command lines can be found in the file Bound_spec_command'[m)[35m;[m[47;9Hdisplay([31m'You must copy the lines from that file into your SWAN INPUT file'[m)[35m;[m[49;166H87,9[10C48%[43;9H[?25h[?25l[49;156HZ[43;9H[?25h[?25l[49;157HZ[43;9H[49;1H[?2004l[49;156H[K[49;1H[?2004l[?1l>[?25h[?1049l[23;0;0t(base) ]0;taran@tarandesktop: ~/Documents/COAWST/Tools/mfiles/swan_forc[01;32mtaran@tarandesktop[00m:[01;34m~/Documents/COAWST/Tools/mfiles/swan_forc[00m$ vim ww3gb_2TPAR.m 
[?2004h[?1049h[22;0;0t[?1h=[?2004h[1;49r[?12h[?12l[27m[23m[29m[m[H[2J[?25l[49;1H"ww3gb_2TPAR.m" [dos] 90L, 3553C[2;1H▽[6n[2;1H  [1;1H[>c]10;?]11;?[1;1H[36mfunction[m ww3gb_2TPAR(modelgrid,yearww3,mmww3,ww3_area,ddww3,specres)

[34m%this assumes data is historical data and is already downloaded to working
%directory[m
[36meval[m([36m[[m[31m'dpname='''[m,ww3_area,[31m'.dp.'[m,yearww3,mmww3,[31m'.grb2'';'[m[36m][m)[35m;[m
[36meval[m([36m[[m[31m'hsname='''[m,ww3_area,[31m'.hs.'[m,yearww3,mmww3,[31m'.grb2'';'[m[36m][m)[35m;[m
[36meval[m([36m[[m[31m'tpname='''[m,ww3_area,[31m'.tp.'[m,yearww3,mmww3,[31m'.grb2'';'[m[36m][m)[35m;[m

hsnc=ncgeodataset(hsname)[35m;[m
tpnc=ncgeodataset(tpname)[35m;[m
dpnc=ncgeodataset(dpname)[35m;[m
xg=dpnc{[31m'lon'[m}(:)[35m;[m[34m%lat of ww3 data[m
xg(xg[38;5;130m>[m[31m0[m)=xg(xg[38;5;130m>[m[31m0[m)[38;5;130m-[m[31m360[m[35m;[m
yg=dpnc{[31m'lat'[m}(:)[35m;[m[34m%lon of ww3 data[m
[36m[[mxg,yg[36m][m=meshgrid(xg,yg)[35m;[m
time=dpnc{[31m'time'[m}(:)[35m;[m[34m%time interval 3 hours[m
time2=datenum(str2num(yearww3),str2num(mmww3),str2num(ddww3)[38;5;130m+[m[31m1[m):[31m3[m[38;5;130m/[m[31m24[m:datenum(str2num(yearww3),str2num(mmww3),str2num(ddww3)[38;5;130m+[m((length(time)[38;5;130m-[m[31m1[m)[38;5;130m/[m([31m24[m[38;5;130m/[m[31m3[m))[38;5;130m+[m[31m1[m)[35m;[m
time=time2[35m;[m
[34m%  limit the length of time.  Could use better logic here
%  for user to set this in ww3_swan_input file.[m
tstart=[31m1[m[35m;[m tend=length(time)[35m;[m
time=time(tstart:tend)[35m;[m

[34m%determine spec pts from grid
% specpoints assumes a masking of 0 for land and NaN for water[m
[36m[[mspecpts[36m][m=ww3_specpoints(modelgrid,specres)[35m;[m

[38;5;130mfor[m i=[31m1[m:length(specpts)
    gx=specpts(i,[31m1[m)[35m;[m
    gy=specpts(i,[31m2[m)[35m;[m
    xl=gx[38;5;130m-[m[31m3[m[35m;[mxr=gx[38;5;130m+[m[31m3[m[35m;[m
    yb=gy[38;5;130m-[m[31m3[m[35m;[myt=gy[38;5;130m+[m[31m3[m[35m;[m[34;5H[34m%determine dimensions of ww3 data needed for interpolation[m
    [36m[[mym xm[36m][m=[38;5;130msize[m(xg)[35m;[m
    ii=find(xg[38;5;130m>=[mxl [38;5;130m&[m xg[38;5;130m<=[mxr [38;5;130m&[m yg[38;5;130m>=[myb [38;5;130m&[m yg[38;5;130m<=[myt)[35m;[mjj=fix((ii[38;5;130m-[m[31m1[m)[38;5;130m/[mym)[38;5;130m+[m[31m1[m[35m;[mii=mod(ii,ym)[35m;[m
    ig0=([38;5;130mmin[m(ii)[38;5;130m-[m[31m1[m)[35m;[m ig1=([38;5;130mmax[m(ii)[38;5;130m+[m[31m1[m)[35m;[m jg0=([38;5;130mmin[m(jj)[38;5;130m-[m[31m1[m)[35m;[m jg1=([38;5;130mmax[m(jj)[38;5;130m+[m[31m1[m)[35m;[m
    irg=[36m[[mnum2str(ig0) [31m':'[m num2str(ig1) [36m][m[35m;[m [34m% irg='[1671:2042]';[m
    jrg=[36m[[mnum2str(jg0) [31m':'[m num2str(jg1) [36m][m[35m;[m [34m% jrg='[2318:2722]';[m
    daplon=xg(ig0:ig1,jg0:jg1)[35m;[m daplat=yg(ig0:ig1,jg0:jg1)[35m;[m
    [38;5;130mclear[m ii jj[35m;[m[43;5H[34m%Interpolate the data to each point and create/write TPAR file[m
    [38;5;130mfor[m wavet=[31m1[m:length(time)
[34m%       eval(['hst=squeeze(hsnc{''Significant_height_of_combined_wind_waves_and_swell''}(wavet,',irg,',',jrg,'));']);[m[46;9H[36meval[m([36m[[m[31m'hst=squeeze(hsnc{''Significant_height_of_combined_wind_waves_and_swell_surface''}(wavet,'[m,irg,[31m','[m,jrg,[31m'));'[m[36m][m)[35m;[m[47;9Hzz=hst[38;5;130m>[m[31m1000[m[35m;[m[48;9Hhst(zz)=[31m0[m[35m;[m [34m%make bad data 0, swan not like NaNs[m[49;166H1,1[11CTop[1;1H[?25hP+q436f\P+q6b75\P+q6b64\P+q6b72\P+q6b6c\P+q2332\P+q2334\P+q2569\P+q2a37\P+q6b31\[?25l[49;156H~@k[1;1H[49;156H   [2;1H[49;166H2,0-1[2;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[2;1H[49;156H   [3;1H[49;166H3,1  [3;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[3;1H[49;156H   [4;1H[49;166H4[4;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[4;1H[49;156H   [5;1H[49;166H5[5;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[5;1H[49;156H   [6;1H[49;166H6[6;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[6;1H[49;156H   [7;1H[49;166H7[7;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[7;1H[49;156H   [8;1H[49;166H8,0-1[8;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[8;1H[49;156H   [9;1H[49;166H9,1  [9;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[9;1H[49;156H   [10;1H[49;166H10,1[10;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[10;1H[49;156H   [11;1H[49;167H1[11;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[11;1H[49;156H   [12;1H[49;167H2[12;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[12;1H[49;156H   [13;1H[49;167H3[13;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[13;1H[49;156H   [14;1H[49;167H4[14;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[14;1H[49;156H   [15;1H[36m[106m[[mxg,yg[36m[106m][m[49;167H5[15;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[15;1H[49;156H   [16;1H[15;1H[36m[[mxg,yg[36m][m[49;167H6[16;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[16;1H[49;156H   [17;1H[49;167H7[17;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[17;1H[49;156H   [18;1H[49;167H8[18;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[18;1H[49;156H   [19;1H[49;167H9[19;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[19;1H[49;156H   [20;1H[49;166H20[20;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[20;1H[49;156H   [21;1H[49;167H1[21;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[21;1H[49;156H   [22;1H[49;167H2[22;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[22;1H[49;156H   [23;1H[49;167H3,0-1[23;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[23;1H[49;156H   [24;1H[49;167H4,1  [24;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[24;1H[49;156H   [25;1H[49;167H5[25;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[25;1H[49;156H   [26;1H[36m[106m[[7C][m[49;167H6[26;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[26;1H[49;156H   [27;1H[26;1H[36m[[7C][m[49;167H7,0-1[27;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[27;1H[49;156H   [28;1H[49;167H8,1  [28;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[28;1H[49;156H   [29;1H[49;167H9[29;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[29;1H[49;156H   [30;1H[49;166H30[30;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[30;1H[49;156H   [31;1H[49;167H1[31;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[31;1H[49;156H   [32;1H[49;167H2[32;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[32;1H[49;156H   [33;1H[49;167H3,0-1[33;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[33;1H[49;156H   [34;1H[49;167H4,1  [34;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[34;1H[49;156H   [35;1H[49;167H5[35;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[35;1H[49;156H   [36;1H[49;167H6[36;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[36;1H[49;156H   [37;1H[49;167H7[37;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[37;1H[49;156H   [38;1H[49;167H8[38;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[38;1H[49;156H   [39;1H[49;167H9[39;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[39;1H[49;156H   [40;1H[49;166H40[40;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[40;1H[49;156H   [41;1H[49;167H1[41;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[41;1H[49;156H   [42;1H[49;167H2[42;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[42;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[49;167H3[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;9HZ1=interp2(daplon,daplat,hst,gx,gy)[35m;[m[49;1H[K[49;166H44,1[11C2%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H
[1;49r[48;9HZ1(isnan(Z1))=[31m0[m[35m;[m[49;166H[K[49;166H45,1[11C4%[43;1H[?25h[?25l[49;156H~@k[43;1H[49;156H   [43;1H[1;48r[48;1H

[?2004h[?1049h[22;0;0t[?1h=[?2004h[1;49r[?12h[?12l[27m[23m[29m[m[H[2J[?25l[49;1H"bdry_com.m" [dos] 22L, 787C[2;1H▽[6n[2;1H  [1;1H[>c]10;?]11;?[1;1H[34m% bdry_com
% This script writes out the boundary statements for TPAR files created
% using ww3_swan_input.m, ww3_specpoints.m, ww3gb_2TPAR.m and ww3nc_2TPAR.m[m

[38;5;130mfor[m bd=[31m1[m:lth
   fprintf(fid,[31m'BOUNDSPEC SEGMENT XY '[m)[35m;[m
   fprintf(fid,[31m'%3.4f %3.4f %3.4f %3.4f '[m,specpts(bd,:))[35m;[m

   pg=num2str(length(num2str(bd)))[35m;[m
   [36meval[m([36m[[m[31m'fprintf(fid,''%'[m,pg,[31m'g'',bd);'[m[36m][m)[35m;[m
   fprintf(fid,[31m'.txt''\n'[m)[35m;[m
[38;5;130mend[m
fprintf(fid,[31m'\n'[m)[35m;[m
fclose(fid)[35m;[m

[?2004h[?1049h[22;0;0t[?1h=[?2004h[1;49r[?12h[?12l[27m[23m[29m[m[H[2J[?25l[49;1H"ww3_specpoints.m" [dos] 101L, 3326C[2;1H▽[6n[2;1H  [1;1H[>c]10;?]11;?[1;1H[36mfunction[m [36m[[mspecpts[36m][m=ww3_specpoints(modelgrid,spec_res)[35m;[m
[34m%*************************************************************************
%this function uses the model grid to determine specpoints along the 
%boundary of the grid which are then used in the loaddap_ww3_2TPAR function
%
%modelgrid=name/location of grid used in the model
%spec_res=number of grid points between spec points/resolution of spec
%points
%
%the output for this functions is saved in the working directory as
%specpts.mat
%
%created by Brandy Armstrong 4/8/09 for use in COAWST system v2
%modified jcw 05Feb2012 to use native matlab netcdf
%*************************************************************************

%load in grid info[m
gx=ncread(modelgrid,[31m'lon_rho'[m)[35m;[mgx2=gx[35m;[m[34m%gx2(gx<0) = gx2(gx<0)+360;[m
gy=ncread(modelgrid,[31m'lat_rho'[m)[35m;[m
[36m[[mxi eta[36m][m=[38;5;130msize[m(gy)[35m;[m
mask=ncread(modelgrid,[31m'mask_rho'[m)[35m;[m
mask(isnan(mask))=[31m1[m[35m;[m
[38;5;130mif[m [38;5;130msize[m(mask)[38;5;130m==[m[31m0[m[35m;[m
    mask=[38;5;130mones[m(xi,eta)[35m;[m
[38;5;130mend[m
gx3=gx2[38;5;130m.*[mmask[35m;[m
gy3=gy[38;5;130m.*[mmask[35m;[m
rr=[31m1[m[35m;[m
